        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 9:18PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 917 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lynn. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Haleyville, Lynn, Double Springs, Lake Buttahatchee, Ashbank,
Ashridge, Natural Bridge, Weiss, Clear Creek, and Delmar.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
